article.headline: Montana 75, Montana-Western 67
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Ryan Staudacher scored a career-high 21 points to help the University of Montana to a 75-67 win over Montana Western. Staudacher went 7-of-12 from the field and was 5-of-7 from 3-point range. Anthony Johnson came off the bench to score 14 points for the Grizzlies (1-1), while Jordan Hasquet and Derek Selvig added 11 points apiece. The Bulldogs (4-3) took their last lead of the game, 31-30, on a 3-pointer by Chad Myers with 2:04 left until halftime. Montana went into the break ahead 34-31. But Western narrowed the gap to 61-60 on a 3-pointer by Myers with 4:34 remaining. The Grizzlies outscored the Bulldogs 12-3 after that and took a 73-63 lead on a free throw by Johnson with 55 seconds left. Terry Hauser came off the bench to lead the Bulldogs with 15 points. Chad Myers and Layne Glaus each scored 13, while Garrett Fink grabbed a team-high eight rebounds.
